  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Sustainable Humanitarian Assistance Program for Ethiopia (SHAPE)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1) Water Chain Management - CHF will train 3 Community Agents from each of the 40 water sites in water chain management. The 120 CAs will attend a training of trainers to become community hygiene facilitators and in turn teach 5,160 household representatives about the importance of safe water and  how to avoid contamination of drinking water.

2) Water Infrastructure Rehabilitation: CHF will rehabilitate 40 shallow wells to improve water availability and access.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The SHAPE program assists agro-pastoralists and pastoralists in Ethiopia&apos;s Somali Regional State to avert the impact of severe food insecurity through improved access to water and income for households affected by drought.

Program Goal: Support economic recovery while increasing resilience to food insecurity and drought, for food insecure Ethiopians.

Objective 1: To increase sustainable income-earning opportunities and improve market linkages.
Objective 2: To increase sustainable agricultural and livestock production
Objective 3: To improve access to safe water and hygiene practices linked to food utilization and livelihoods</narrative>
  </description>
